citation: Proclamation under the Youth Justice (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2013 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Youth Justice (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2013

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Youth Justice (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2013 fix 1 March 2014 as the day on which the provisions of that Act, except sections 18, 19 and 44, commence.

3 February 2014

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

MICHELLE O'BYRNE

Minister for Children

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 12 February 2014

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Health and Human Services.
